The Commodity Futures Trading Commission approved Minneapolis Grain Exchange's application trade high fructose corn syrup-55 , HFCS-55 , future contract , commission said .
The contract provides delivery 48,000 lb , plus minus two pct , bulk HFCS-55 meeting specified standard regarding physical chemical property .
CFTC said exchange plan begin trading July 1987 HFCS-55 contract April 6 .
CFTC said soft drink industry currently buy least 95 pct U.S.-produced HFCS-55 , liquid food beverage sweetener produced processing corn starch corn refiner .
